Follow `.saitec/AI_COLLABORATION.md` as the single source of truth.
Use `.saitec/Skills.md` for Git workflow expectations.

- Read the relevant code and docs before editing.
- If the task involves branches, commits, PRs, or delivery summaries, read `.saitec/Skills.md`.
- Keep changes minimal and consistent with existing repository patterns.
- Do not fabricate APIs, commands, environment state, or validation results.
- Report what changed, how it was validated, and what risks remain.
- If a tool-specific instruction conflicts with the main collaboration guide, prefer `.saitec/AI_COLLABORATION.md`.
